Review.create({ title: "Fans of Fern Michaels' Sisterhood series won't be disappointed..", rating: 4, body: "Fans of Fern Michaels' Sisterhood series won't be disappointed...this is a typically good entry. No, Michaels isn't the world's greatest writer--as she admits--but she sure knows how to tell a heckuva engaging story, and you come to care about the characters, no matter how wooden the dialogue.My only disappointment with this particular book is that there were too many rehashes. The team would learn something, and then someone would summarize it all for them. It seemed to be needlessly padding the book--maybe Michaels had a word minimum she had to hit? Because of the space taken up with rehashes, this particular book has a bit less depth than some of Michaels' other Sisterhood books.", user_id: user11.id, book_id: book42.id })
