Review.create({ title: "Original content", rating: 5, body: "A lot of the stuff in this volume doesn't come from the webcomic. Actually, I'm pretty sure ALL of it is new stuff. Nevertheless, it is really funny and action packed. This volume features a lot of Garo actually hunting heroes. You can think of it as filler I guess, but it's necessary in order to not run out of material.But this volume has 3 significant breaks in canon from the webcomic: allows Garo and Saitama to encounter one another before the big final battle, Saitama learns about the human monster threat and gets motivated to do something about it, Garo develops a rapport with a kid as he hunts heroes. That development with the kid is especially significant and I think it's an excellent addition. The passing encounter with Saitama is almost immediately ret conned and is just played for laughs, but it is there.", user_id: user16.id, book_id: book73.id })
