Review.create({ title: "4.5 Stars", rating: 4, body: "A book about love, loss, letting go and finding love again. This love story/mystery is well written and kept me guessing. I&#8217;d be convinced that the outcome/reason behind a particular event would be one of two things just to be proven wrong.I liked all of the characters, but at the same time none were above suspicion. Ian for example: He is a photographer who sells his photos for large sums of money yet is willing to take a job at a coffee shop. Is he just a nice guy? Is he doing it for love? Or is he part of some bigger plan/conspiracy? Then there&#8217;s Thomas. Is he James&#8217; caring brother who is concerned about Aimee? Or has he something to hide?Is James really gone or is it an elaborate conspiracy? Why does everyone seem convinced that Lacy is lying about James and how many, if any, know what really happened?I really enjoyed this book and when I got to about the 50% mark, I wasn&#8217;t able to put it down. I did find the epilogue to be a little strange. I hope it was there in order to clarify earlier event(s) in the book and not to lead into a sequel. I&#8217;m not sure I&#8217;d want to see things shaken up again.", user_id: user11.id, book_id: book79.id })
Review.create({ title: "Everything we keep", rating: 5, body: "Very good book much to my surprise. One of those kind of books that you are carrying around to squeeze in another chapter between daily life. Did not expect the twist at the end and was very happy to have it or it would have been just another romance novel. Was it totally believable, not really. I can't imagine a wanna be boyfriend hanging on for that long and going through that much for a women he barely knows let alone all the work it involved to stay near her. But I certainly wanted to believe it. Aimee seemed so confused most of the time but  finally moved forward. A bit heartbreaking but thoroughly enjoyable read.", user_id: user12.id, book_id: book79.id })
