Review.create({ title: "Intriguing...", rating: 4, body: "Oh my what a saga... ! Is it Downtown Abbey or Flowers in the attic?! This book asks...Is it possible to be haunted by the future?The year is 1928. From the most innocent flirtation on a boat bound for the US... the two most unlikely pair - Matthew and Kate become acquainted...&#34;Why would someone like him be interested in someone like you? I had no answer. There was nothing to set me apart from the hundreds of prettier, more sophisticated girls Matthew must have met in his lifetime. I still couldn&#8217;t quite believe it myself.&#34;Kate Moore is looking for a way out of the poverty of her childhood. When an incredible encounter on a boat brings her face-to-face with the handsome heir - Matthew Lemont she thinks she may have found her escape&#8212;as long as she can keep her past concealed. The Lemonts have this motto, &#8216;It is done.&#8217; It means they always get their way. Kate realises soon after moving into Lakecrest - the family manor that she has hardly escaped at all. She fears the home, the family and especially her mother-in-law - Hannah. &#34;Hannah looks at me sometimes like she&#8217;s biding her time until the baby comes, but after that, who knows? They have this cell in the basement, and she could lock me up, anytime, without anyone knowing. She&#8217;s got all sorts of doctors in her pocket who could declare me crazy.&#34;I simply adore our heroine, there is an ongoing theme through-out the novel of relying on herself and making her own luck, she was incredibly self determined... &#34;I had to pretend none of that mattered. I&#8217;d risen above the miseries of my childhood because I was determined not to let my past define my future. Self-confidence was the only advantage I had.&#34;Elizabeth Blackwell is a story-telling genius.Read more &rsaquo;", user_id: user2.id, book_id: book85.id })
