Review.create({ title: "She marries him early on before she really gets to know anything about him and grows to regret this decision more times then nau", rating: 4, body: "A story that will hold your interest! The mystery of uncovering the secrets of the disappearance of Aunt kept the pages turning and had me glued to figure out all the sordid details of the Lemont family's past including mental illness, disappearances and skeletons.Kate is a young woman who meets a dashing and wealthy man on a boat. He is everything she has grown up to want and will sweep her away into a life of luxury and class. She marries him early on before she really gets to know anything about him and grows to regret this decision more times then naught feeling like a captive in her own home between her mother in law and sister in law. Kate is a great complex and deep character that really comes to life. At first, I wasn't very sure how to feel about her since she gave off the gold digging vibe, but as the story progresses you really get an insight to her character and how she is a survivor and a fighter, not one to just sit about, but digs deep to uncover all the mysteries at Lakecrest.", user_id: user4.id, book_id: book85.id })
