Review.create({ title: "Quick but dark read", rating: 3, body: "I chose this as my Kindle First selection and it is a very quick read. However, it is a very dark gothic read. If you use the look inside feature and read the the prologue you might get the wrong idea about this book. The prologue focuses on Kate and her children but this book focuses on the time before they are born. After a quick set up in which Kate and Mathew meet and marry the book focuses on Kate moving into the family estate. Kate was penniless and focused on improving her life but now must face the consequences of getting what she thought she wanted. In this case it's the husband with his very real troubles. The sister-in-law with her own issues and a liking to bring Kate down. The mother-in-law that controls everyone and will do whatever it takes to keep things as she wants. While Kate must adjust to her new circumstances the book is really about the mysterious disappearance of her husband's Aunt Cecily many years ago. What happened to Cecily becomes the focus Kate's attention and that of the book. As a Kindle First book I have no complaints. It was what I expected for the most part from the description. This is a very gothic book and should only be read if you are in the mood for dark and brooding.", user_id: user10.id, book_id: book85.id })
