Review.create({ title: "Rumor is that Sayers got tired of Lord Peter in his happy go lucky batchelor mode and wanted to drop him", rating: 4, body: "This is the second Lord Peter mystery in which Harriet Vane appears.  (The first was Strong Poison).  The introduction of an important female charachter  represents a major shift in the tone of the series.  Rumor is that Sayers got tired of Lord Peter in his happy go lucky batchelor mode and wanted to drop him.  He was too popular.  She couldn't. do it.  .  Instead she made him into a more solid, serious character capable of developing serious relationships with someone other than his valet.  At this point the books began to be novels rather than simple who dunnits.  Thee characters become more complex as the series goes on.  There is still bloody murder however and its a treat for readers who like intricate puzzles.", user_id: user11.id, book_id: book96.id })
