book115 = Book.create({ title: "The Meryton Murders: A Mystery Set in the Town of Jane Austen's Pride &amp; Prejudice", author: "Victoria Grossack", image_url: "https://res.cloudinary.com/dt72mzjpx/image/upload/book_115.jpg", publisher: "", date: "", description: " Elizabeth Darcy receives a letter from her father informing her that her sister needs her. So Elizabeth travels from Pemberley to her old neighborhood to do what she can to support her sister in her time of distress. After her arrival, an acquaintance apparently kills herself, a cousin is found dead, and tempers everywhere are frayed. Soon Elizabeth learns first-hand what is menacing Meryton, and her fortune, her marriage, and even her life are at risk.&#x22;Grossack's writing is spot on when it comes to capturing Jane Austen's tone and writing style.&#x22; Cozy Mystery Book Reviews.", amazon_link: "https://www.amazon.com/Meryton-Murders-Mystery-Austens-Prejudice-ebook/dp/B01BRRTA2I", kobo_link: "https://www.kobo.com/us/en/search?query=The%20Meryton%20Murders:%20A%20Mystery%20Set%20in%20the%20Town%20of%20Jane%20Austen's%20Pride%20&amp;%20Prejudice%20Victoria%20Grossack", play_link: "https://play.google.com/store/search?c=books&hl=en&q=The%20Meryton%20Murders:%20A%20Mystery%20Set%20in%20the%20Town%20of%20Jane%20Austen's%20Pride%20&amp;%20Prejudice%20Victoria%20Grossack" })
Review.create({ title: "This is a fun read and holds your attention all the way through", rating: 5, body: "This is a fun read and holds your attention all the way through.  Lots of twists and turns and not at all predictable.  It prompted me to go back and reread Pride and Prejudice.  The Meryton Murders is a nice logical continuation of that classic by Jane Austin.  I highly recommend this book, well written and I think Jane Austin would approve of Victoria Grossack's writing style and plot!I have read all of Victoria's books and enjoyed each and every one of them.  I am eagerly awaiting her next addtion to the Tapestry in Bronze series.", user_id: user1.id, book_id: book115.id })
Review.create({ title: "Mysterious and wonderful", rating: 5, body: "Unusual happenings in this version make for a sit-on-the-end-of-your-seat reading.  This was interesting, fun and intriguing!  Cannot wait for your next book!", user_id: user2.id, book_id: book115.id })
Review.create({ title: "Back to Meryton", rating: 4, body: "I am an unabashed Jane Austen fan, so I read any book that is a take-off on any of Austen's novels. Victoria Grossack has produced one of the better take-offs of Pride & Prejudice. Since I feel as if I know the characters, I think the they were as developed as they could be without making up new personalities. Sometimes the plot seemed a bit forced, but it is an altogether a fun and a good read.", user_id: user3.id, book_id: book115.id })
Review.create({ title: "Anyone that loves the style of Jane Austen will love this mystery", rating: 5, body: "Anyone that loves the style of Jane Austen will love this mystery. The characters are very true to the time period and really work as &#34;continuing&#34; the story Jane Austen started. I loved the first of this series and was very glad to see it continue - already looking forward to the next. These books can be read as stand alones, but once you get to know the characters - you just want to see what happens to them next! A very good read.", user_id: user4.id, book_id: book115.id })
Review.create({ title: "Another great read, written in the style of Jane Austen.", rating: 5, body: "I enjoyed this book enormously.It is equally as good as &#34;The Highbury Murders&#34; by the same author.The plot is well conceived and the writing first class,", user_id: user5.id, book_id: book115.id })
Review.create({ title: "VIrtue triumphs over vice.", rating: 5, body: "I enjoyed this book, and I think other Austen lovers will too.  It is fast-paced, funny, and the characters sound and act just like they did in the original.  They have moved on, though, from the end of P&P.  Jane is expecting her first child, and Elizabeth is dealing with the awkwardness of being much richer than nearly everyone she knows.  Then it becomes more than awkward as she is the target of blackmail.  As in P&P, Darcy and Elizabeth are separated for much of the story, but this is a mystery, not a romance, and I was happy to see how happy they are together.  Darcy does get to save the day, arriving at just the right moment on a galloping horse (although he was coming for another reason).  A treat for those who like P&P!", user_id: user6.id, book_id: book115.id })
Review.create({ title: "Mystery that captures Jane Austen's style and characters.", rating: 5, body: "Very cleverly written and a good read. Even though I am not a fan of Jane Austen this kept me going so that I took off a whole afternoon to finish it.", user_id: user7.id, book_id: book115.id })
Review.create({ title: "and it was SUCH a delight to sink into the familiar prose and comfortable world ...", rating: 5, body: "Im not generally a fan of murder mysteries, but I am a fan of Jane Austen, and it was SUCH a delight to sink into the familiar prose and comfortable world of characters with all their foibles, and then the next thing you knew I was eagerly turning the pages to see what we would find out next! Ms. Grossack has produced quite a wonder here, with her feel for Jane Austen and her ability to recreate that world, and her imagination in adding a little twist of her own to keep us guessing. A pure delight! Thank you to her, and enjoy!", user_id: user8.id, book_id: book115.id })
book117 = Book.create({ title: "Feversong: A Fever Novel", author: "Karen Marie Moning", image_url: "https://res.cloudinary.com/dt72mzjpx/image/upload/book_117.jpg", publisher: "Delacorte Press ", date: "January 17, 2017", description: " MacKayla Lane and Jericho Barrons return in the epic conclusion to the pulse-pounding Fever series, where a world thrown into chaos grows more treacherous at every turn.As Mac, Barrons, Ryodan, and Jada struggle to restore control, enemies become allies, right and wrong cease to exist, and the lines between life and death, lust and love, disappear completely.&#160;Black holes loom menacingly over Dublin, threatening to destroy the earth, yet the greatest danger is the one MacKayla Lane has unleashed from within: The Sinsar Dubh&mdash;a sentient book of unthinkable evil&mdash;has possessed her body and will stop at nothing in its insatiable quest for power.&#160;  The fate of Man and Fae rests on destroying the book and recovering the long-lost Song of Making, the sole magic that can repair the fragile fabric of the earth. But to achieve these aims, sidhe-seers, the Nine, Seelie, and Unseelie must form unlikely alliances and make heart-wrenching choices. For Barrons and Jada, this means finding the Seelie queen, who alone can wield the mysterious song, negotiating with a lethal Unseelie prince hell-bent on ruling the Fae courts, and figuring out how to destroy the Sinsar Dubh while keeping Mac alive.  This time, there&rsquo;s no gain without sacrifice, no pursuit without risk, no victory without irrevocable loss. In the battle for Mac&rsquo;s soul, every decision exacts a tremendous price.Look for all of Karen Marie Moning&rsquo;s sensational Fever novels: DARKFEVER | BLOODFEVER | FAEFEVER | DREAMFEVER | SHADOWFEVER | ICED | BURNED | FEVERBORN | FEVERSONG", amazon_link: "https://www.amazon.com/Feversong-Fever-Karen-Marie-Moning-ebook/dp/B01D7CJ43G", kobo_link: "https://www.kobo.com/us/en/search?query=Feversong:%20A%20Fever%20Novel%20Karen%20Marie%20Moning", play_link: "https://play.google.com/store/search?c=books&hl=en&q=Feversong:%20A%20Fever%20Novel%20Karen%20Marie%20Moning" })
Review.create({ title: "Wonderfully satisfying ride on a true emotional rollercoaster.", rating: 5, body: "I just finished reading Feversong. It wasn't what I expected it to be. It was better. What an outstanding culmination of an extraordinary series.  It was certainly an emotional rollercoaster ride, and I'm still processing how I feel. Few books have left me this emotionally drained, yet satisfied that the story has a true ending which is also a new beginning. As much as I've loved all of the books, I'm at peace with this resolution.  I'm just sad that it's over.", user_id: user1.id, book_id: book117.id })
Review.create({ title: "Epic Adventure!", rating: 5, body: "A fabulous book filled with adventure, magic, epic love, and family. Terrific final book to a great series. Best I've read!What a ride this series has been!  Amazing author.", user_id: user2.id, book_id: book117.id })
Review.create({ title: "Read this series", rating: 5, body: "I had my ups and downs in this series, but man what an ending. There's so many things that I love about this book and a number of things that make me a little bit frustrated.So here's what I left: I love that Mac and Barron's finally get there happily ever after. I really feel like their story has come to an end and I'm happy with it. I like the level of character growth and development for all the characters who are given a Birdseye view have. I love that I was so emotionally attached to this book that I actually cried.What I'm disappointed with: why were we given more character perspective from The point of view of, LOR, KAT, And maybe even Jo.  Also while I may not be disappointed, there better be another book for Ryondan and Danny.While the book really ties up Mac and Barron's I was disappointed with all that open loopholes for all the other characters. It is my hope that the author intends to use these openings to write further into the fever series. As far as I'm aware there will be at least two more books for the characters past Mac.", user_id: user3.id, book_id: book117.id })
Review.create({ title: "Wow!", rating: 5, body: "This is a beautiful conclusion to an amazing series! I loved every page. The evolution of each character, from series beginning to end, feels authentic and satisfying. I cried, laughed and sat in awe as these characters exceeded even my highest hopes for them. Ryodan takes leading man status to a whole new level in this book because of his selfless love and understanding. Mac grows into herself and her relationship with Barrons. The dimensions of Cruce are on full display and intriguing. Dani, however, was the highlight of this book for me. I sincerely hope to read more about her journey in the future.", user_id: user4.id, book_id: book117.id })
Review.create({ title: "A satisfying ending to a great series!", rating: 5, body: "Karen Marie Moning completely redeemed herself with the last installment of her series. I had the best time finding out how she would complete all the storylines. So bittersweet! I won't say more to spoil it for you. I'm going to miss the Fever world!!!! Guess it's time to go back and read it all again from the beginning ", user_id: user5.id, book_id: book117.id })
Review.create({ title: "Fecking amazing Batman.", rating: 5, body: "Beautifully written, this book possessed me as I ran along with each character. Ups and downs, good and bad I worshiped each page and laughed and cried with them. As a fever fan I loved this book and can not wait for what she has next in plan.", user_id: user6.id, book_id: book117.id })
Review.create({ title: "This is the grand finale to a fantastic story. I'm just sorry it's over", rating: 5, body: "OH! MY! GOD!  So much information to process.  This is the grand finale to a fantastic story.  I'm just sorry it's over.  I hope there are still books to come where these characters come into play.  I hope we have more of the Keltar and Fae world.", user_id: user7.id, book_id: book117.id })
Review.create({ title: "Epic Finale!", rating: 5, body: "I don't even know what to say or how to express my emotions after finishing this book and knowing it's the end of the series. The culmination of this story and the evolution of MacKayla Lane was everything I could have hoped for. I cried at more than one part and the early parts of thisbook had me so stressed. God how I wish Jericho Barrons was a real man! I can only hope that someday we might get more if these characters. I was left with many questions and I NEED more of Ryodan. Please KMM don't let this be the end!", user_id: user8.id, book_id: book117.id })
book118 = Book.create({ title: "While You Were Sleeping: A gripping psychological thriller you just can't put down", author: "Kathryn Croft", image_url: "https://res.cloudinary.com/dt72mzjpx/image/upload/book_118.jpg", publisher: "Bookouture ", date: "November 16, 2016", description: " Yesterday your life was perfect.  Today you&#x2019;ll find out that was all a lie.A gripping, shocking psychological thriller, with a twist that will take you by surprise. For fans of Gone Girl, The Girl on the Train and Behind Closed Doors.Tara Logan adores her perfect little family: husband, Noah, and two children, teenager Rosie and eleven-year-old Spencer.&#xa0;But her happiness is shattered when she wakes up one morning in her neighbour&#x2019;s bed, with no memory of how she got there or what happened between them.&#xa0;And worse &#x2013; he has been&#xa0;stabbed to death.Convinced she didn&#x2019;t kill Lee and scared of losing everything she cares about, Tara flees home and stays silent, holding her breath as the investigation grips the neighbourhood.But as her daughter spirals out of control, and her husband becomes increasingly distant, Tara starts to wonder if someone in her life&#xa0;knows what really happened&#xa0;that night. When the police turn their questions towards her, Tara realises she has to find out. But what will it take to uncover the real story, and can she survive the truth?Read what everyone is saying about While You Were Sleeping&#x2018;WOW!!!!!!! I literally could not put this book down. I read it from start to finish in one sitting &#x2026; I found myself holding my breath, peeking through my closed eyes at what I was about to read next &#x2026; a phenomenal thriller &#x2026; I was beyond shocked by the ending, I had to pick my jaw up off the ground!&#x2019; 5 stars &#x2013; Goodreads Reviewer&#x2018;Omg! If you read only one book this year, make it this one. It is simply superb! I thought I knew what was going to happen but OMG I was so wrong. Make sure you don't miss this one!&#x2019; 5 stars &#x2013; Goodreads Reviewer&#x2018;Whoa! Talk about a fast-paced narrative that kept me up all night. Loved the mystery and suspense!!&#x2019; A Bookish Way of Life'A riveting psychological crime thriller&#x2026;suspenseful, absorbing and utterly entertaining. I loved it.&#x2019; Writes Escape &#x2018;A full on twisted thriller which had me hooked from the first page&#x2026;I quite honestly whizzed through this in one evening as once I had started I didn&#x2019;t want to stop reading.&#x2019; Jen Med&#x2019;s Book Reviews&#x2018;There are so many twists and turns in this story my heart was literally pounding&#x2026; I couldn&#x2019;t turn the pages fast enough so I could find out who the murderer actually was and it was well worth the wait&#x2026; a brilliant psychological thriller that had me gripped and guessing right until the very end. It is a fast paced read that will have your heart racing. Loved it!&#x2019; By the Letter Book Reviews &#x2018;Hypnotizing from the very first page &#x2026; so intense, that you are left reeling. I found myself flipping through the pages as quickly as I could read so I could find out what was happening.&#x2019; Clues and Reviews", amazon_link: "https://www.amazon.com/While-You-Were-Sleeping-psychological-ebook/dp/B01M7NO5QM", kobo_link: "https://www.kobo.com/us/en/search?query=While%20You%20Were%20Sleeping:%20A%20gripping%20psychological%20thriller%20you%20just%20can't%20put%20down%20Kathryn%20Croft", play_link: "https://play.google.com/store/search?c=books&hl=en&q=While%20You%20Were%20Sleeping:%20A%20gripping%20psychological%20thriller%20you%20just%20can't%20put%20down%20Kathryn%20Croft" })
Review.create({ title: "Not great but decent read", rating: 3, body: "I didn't find it that gripping of a thriller. It was a decent book, but not all that unusual.", user_id: user1.id, book_id: book118.id })
Review.create({ title: "Bookworm", rating: 4, body: "This as an excellent book with many twists and turns.  I recommend this novel.  Hope to read more by Kathryn Croft.", user_id: user2.id, book_id: book118.id })
Review.create({ title: "NUMEROUS TWISTS & TURNS", rating: 5, body: "When Tara Logan wakes up naked in a strange bed, and then realizes that there is a man in bed with her, she panics. For the man is her neighbor Lee Jacobs, and he is dead. Stabbed with a knife. And she has no memory of what, if anything, went on between her and Lee. Plus, there is not a drop of blood on her.Thus begins the twisted tale that only gets more complex as time goes by. First, Tara decides to say nothing, hoping that the police will find whoever killed Lee. For she is sure that she didn&#8217;t. Not because she knows what happened, because she doesn&#8217;t.While You Were Sleeping: A gripping psychological thriller you just can't put down, set in and around London, is the kind of story full of characters you can suspect. It might have been Lee&#8217;s wife Serena. They had been having trouble.Or perhaps it could have been Tara and Noah&#8217;s daughter Rosie, who has been behaving oddly. Even more so than usual, and she finally &#8220;confessed&#8221; that Lee had been hitting on her, but denied that anything had happened. However, when someone lies as much as Rosie does, it&#8217;s hard to believe anything she says. Then, from one moment to the next, Rosie&#8217;s story changes. She is also very horrible to her mother most of the time, so it would be easy to believe she had done something this despicable.At one point, Mikey, a coworker of Tara&#8217;s, appears to be stalking her, and pushing for a relationship. He claims to have damaging information he could give the police. Could he know more because he was the actual killer?Meanwhile, something has happened to Tara&#8217;s sister Lisa; she shows up covered with bruises.Read more &rsaquo;", user_id: user3.id, book_id: book118.id })
Review.create({ title: "Only thing I liked is that the killer was unexpected", rating: 2, body: "Yawn fest. Whole thing could have been written in about 3 chapters. Only thing I liked is that the killer was unexpected.", user_id: user4.id, book_id: book118.id })
Review.create({ title: "Wow, didn't expect that!", rating: 5, body: "This was my first book to read by this author. I chose it on a whim and was interested more after reading reviews.  I love a good mystery, but am usually able to figure it out by the end of the story. This one kept me second-guessing until the end!.  Great character development!  I will definitely read more by this author.", user_id: user5.id, book_id: book118.id })
Review.create({ title: " moments - and not in a good way. Plenty of scenes to roll your eyes ...", rating: 2, body: "Way too many &#34;are you kidding me?&#34; moments - and not in a good way.  Plenty of scenes to roll your eyes at.  Felt no connection to characters, story started off interesting and was extremely forced by the end.  Been getting way too many duds from Amazon &#34;recommendations&#34; lately.  Glad I only paid 99 cents.", user_id: user6.id, book_id: book118.id })
Review.create({ title: "Too much like a Lifetime Movie for my tastes", rating: 3, body: "The book started out with an interesting premise. A woman named Tara wakes up in bed with a dead man and doesn't remember how she got there. He turns out to be her neighbor Lee. From that point there were so many red herrings that it started to feel contrived. There was a daughter who lies about everything and a detective who doesn't behave in a professional way.  Tara decides not to tell anyone about the fact that she was there when Lee was murdered even when her daughter is a suspect. The wife of the murdered man refuses to talk to Tara but talked to Tara's daughter in the middle of the night. It started to seem silly to me.", user_id: user7.id, book_id: book118.id })
Review.create({ title: "Five Stars", rating: 5, body: "Wow!", user_id: user8.id, book_id: book118.id })
Review.create({ title: "Unexpected", rating: 5, body: "I'm a sucker for twists and turns that are not cliche and unpredictable. That's this book. I'm looking forward to reading more from Kathryn!", user_id: user9.id, book_id: book118.id })
Review.create({ title: "Five Stars", rating: 5, body: "Found it near impossible to put down", user_id: user10.id, book_id: book118.id })
Review.create({ title: "The daughter's character was annoying and not believable", rating: 2, body: "Was not impressed. About 90% through I ended up skimming to the end. The daughter's character was annoying and not believable. Other ideas in the book did not make sense and were questionable. Poor writing.", user_id: user11.id, book_id: book118.id })
Review.create({ title: "Twists and turns", rating: 4, body: "A good read full of surprises. I would definitely recommend to a friend.Just when you think you figured it out, another twist!", user_id: user12.id, book_id: book118.id })
Review.create({ title: "Annoyed", rating: 1, body: "The writing style of this book was very distracting.  I can't describe it, but it's like when an author only uses said to describe conversing... it's told in the first person, but not as if you were inside their head, hearing their thoughts, but as if they were speaking aloud every thought as it comes.I like to get carried away by a story, but in this one, I was constantly irritated by the narrative.The main character also has some fatal flaws that kept me from liking her, she was alternately making stupid or impetuous decisions and couldn't decide if she was going to be the always supportive mom or the one that throws her kid under a bus for no reason.... the only reason I finished this book was to find out who the killer was, but along the way, I thought the police on this story must be total morons. ..", user_id: user13.id, book_id: book118.id })
Review.create({ title: "What happens when we lie...", rating: 4, body: "This suspense-filled novel about the repercussions of dishonesty kept me engaged. The major characters were well developed, and I could visualize them. There were many plot twists I did not see coming. Yet there were hints that careful readers will ferret out.What was missing were the little details that set the scene, that tell the story in subtle ways. It was hard for me to get a handle on how things looked. The material things we surround ourselves with help tell our story. They were rather scant here.Otherwise, well worth your time.", user_id: user14.id, book_id: book118.id })
Review.create({ title: "Terrible book. Dragged on and on", rating: 1, body: "Terrible book.  Dragged on and on.  Couldn't be bothered reading it all, just looked at the end to see whodunit.", user_id: user15.id, book_id: book118.id })
Review.create({ title: "Thoroughly enjoyable read.", rating: 5, body: "Fabulous!  I had no idea.  Completely unsuspecting.  What ?  How did Kathryn Crofton come up with this ending?  I believed until the ending that it was definitely someone else.  An unlikable person at that.  An unsympathetic character at best.  Thank you, Ms. Crofton.  Thoroughly enjoyable read.", user_id: user16.id, book_id: book118.id })
