Review.create({ title: "Reviewed by Christine at [...]", rating: 4, body: "Alex Cold Fury Hockey book one by Sawyer Bennett is my first book by this author but definitely not my last!This is the story of Alex and Sutton.....Their path to a HEA was not an easy one.....Alex plays hockey for the Cold Fury, a North Carolina team. Alex is cold-hearted, rude and has no real friends. In fact, he isn't even liked by the team's fans. Does he care? Absolutely not! Alex doesn't want or need friends. He doesn't want or need fans AND he certainly doesn't want a relationship. Alex may be okay with the animosity he is causing around him however, team management is not. Because of his bad attitude, Alex is required to do community service; he will be the spokesperson of a new drug-abuse awareness program.Sutton is the social worker Alex has to work with. I really liked Sutton. Sutton is able to see through Alex's bad-boy facade because of her personal and professional experiences.As Alex and Sutton begin to work together, a friendship develops then turns into something more intense. Alex was not an easy man to like. In fact it was damn difficult. There were times in the book that I was so angry with him, but there were even more times that I wanted to hug his pain away. That being said, I loved watching the ice around Alex's heart melt away. Alex made some bad decisions but by the end of the novel he more than made up for them in a way that was sweet, romantic and oh so swoon worthy.Alex is written in dual POV and is the first in the Cold Fury Hockey series with seven books listed as of now. However, books one through five are currently released.", user_id: user6.id, book_id: book154.id })
Review.create({ title: "&#10084;", rating: 5, body: "I loved it !", user_id: user7.id, book_id: book154.id })
Review.create({ title: "4 Stars ****", rating: 4, body: "I am really enjoying Cold Fury, Alex and Sutton&#8217;s story was great!!", user_id: user8.id, book_id: book154.id })
Review.create({ title: "Heartbreaker Alex", rating: 5, body: "Alex hate hockey and he doesn't give a damn about anything, but he is the MVP on his team. The suits upstairs, as the coach calls them is not happy with his attitude and he's forced to cooperate with Sutton in building a anti-drug-abuse campaign and be their spokesman. The chemistry between them are instantly affecting them.........I loved this book and I almost always do with Bennett's books, they are full of emotions and I feel like they are written with a lot of love and care. The characters are described with so much feelings and in such a colourful way that I clearly see them in my mind.The writing style is as excellent as always, easy to read and no unnecessary descriptions of surroundings. And dialogues......yes!!!!The storyline is good, two people with a lot of baggage after a rough childhood, one of them has worked through it and one is just ignoring it. The understanding Sutton is showing Alex when he struggles to find  his way is remarkable and that makes me feel a little unsettled but this is fiction so I choose to see it as it is and enjoy it.When a book makes me cry and laugh and occasionally hot and bothered *blushing* it's a great 5 star read.This is the first book in a series but it's a HEA so don't fear...... I initially started to read this one because I've received an ARC of the last book in this series and I love this author so I thought I should try to read the first books before I jump to the last. I don't regret that decision but my credit card might be......... Consider me gone the next week or so:-)", user_id: user9.id, book_id: book154.id })
