Review.create({ title: "An enjoyable read", rating: 5, body: "This is a wonderfully heartwarming story about finding yourself and the love that follows. I couldn't put the book down until it was finished", user_id: user8.id, book_id: book167.id })
Review.create({ title: "Family Tree: A Novel", rating: 5, body: "This is written so well. It gives an insight to something very few have ever been a part off. A year in a coma.", user_id: user9.id, book_id: book167.id })
Review.create({ title: "Sweet as syrup", rating: 3, body: "This is a warm book, although a fair amount is set in cold Vermont winters that will make your teeth chatter. Annie escaped the family maple sugar farm when she went off to college, her heart filled with dreams. A decade later, it seems as if her dreams have been (mostly) realized, but nothing is perfect. When imperfection turns to betrayal, rage, and tragedy, she winds up back where she started. Some things haven't changed - the maple sugar farm is there, the small town and the people in it, including her high school sweetheart. Has Annie changed? Is she willing to try for a different future, recapture the past, or be trapped by the recent present? I enjoyed this book and found much of it rang true emotionally, but it isn't so outstanding that I'd want to reread it. Fans of the author should be very pleased with it, and anyone who has ever had any curiosity about maple syrup will absolutely love it.", user_id: user10.id, book_id: book167.id })
Review.create({ title: "I really enjoy Susan Wiggs books and this one kept my interest ...", rating: 5, body: "I really enjoy Susan Wiggs books and this one kept my interest through the entire book. If you like to read books that tell a story you can relate to you should enjoy this one.", user_id: user11.id, book_id: book167.id })
