book193 = Book.create({ title: "Falling for the Babysitter", author: "Penny Wylder", image_url: "https://res.cloudinary.com/dt72mzjpx/image/upload/book_193.jpg", publisher: "", date: "", description: " My next door neighbor is a single dad. A very, VERY hot single dad.And he wants me to be his babysitter.I could use the extra money so that part's easy. What's NOT easy is the fact I've had a crush on Deacon for years. He never knew, and it never mattered. I was too young then.But I'm not now.He looks at me like he wants to rip my clothes straight off. His brother hates me, though--thinks I'm no good, just another woman trying to wreck Deacon's life. If he catches us together, he'll probably throw him AND his cute daughter out on the street just to prove a point.I can't let that happen.But after seeing Deacon shirtless... noticing how stiff his whole body gets around me... I'm not sure I can keep resisting.Or if I even want to.This is a standalone novella with a HEA and NO cheating!Penny Wylder writes just that-- wild romances. Happily Ever Afters are always better when they're a little dirty, so if you're looking for a page turner that will make you feel naughty in all the right places, jump right in and leave your panties at the door!", amazon_link: "https://www.amazon.com/Falling-Babysitter-Penny-Wylder-ebook/dp/B01N4KQHDI", kobo_link: "https://www.kobo.com/us/en/search?query=Falling%20for%20the%20Babysitter%20Penny%20Wylder", play_link: "https://play.google.com/store/search?c=books&hl=en&q=Falling%20for%20the%20Babysitter%20Penny%20Wylder" })
Review.create({ title: "Sad", rating: 1, body: "Never read any of her books before this one. I willNot purchase another one. There was no depth toThis story. I have read short steamy novellas and this one had me skimming through the pages saying to myself WTF. The main character has a crush on her neighbor since she was a child, ok we can work with that, but then there was no more story just straight to first encounter like she was rushing the story. The characters  first encounter was tooFast and nothing built up to it, they are talking about getting pregnant during the first encounter it was weird and creepy. The only one who had sense in the book was the brother until he didn't. It went from bad to worse. I was not impressed. I read a lot and I have read some good and some bad and this one was just a really crappy story line.  I think if she has beta readers or friends reading her books before she publishes then she needs new people. The type who won't always be agreeable but give honest feedback. Anyone can hit publish on Amazon but to build a fan base and give readers something to look forward to requires more effort. I wasted my time reading this book. I would hope the author would maybe try reaching out to other people and get some real feedback before her next novel.", user_id: user1.id, book_id: book193.id })
Review.create({ title: "Not My Cup of Tea", rating: 1, body: "I have enjoyed some of Penny's other books, but I just could not get excited about a 30-year old man coming on to a barely legal immature girl. She thought of herself as more of an old soul, but most of the things she says and does sound like she's still 13.  If this were my daughter, I'd want to kill that man. I do not see any hotness factor in that much older man wanting to impregnate in immature innocent teenage virgin. I couldn't finish it. Maybe if she had been 24, it might have worked for me.", user_id: user2.id, book_id: book193.id })
Review.create({ title: "Hot Sexy Read", rating: 4, body: "There is just something about a Tabbo romance. Remy has had a crush on Deacon since she was 13 when he lived next door. Well Deacon has moved back and he isn't alone he has he sweet little baby girl Bailey. Can a relationship last with a big age difference, well.grab this story to see what happens.", user_id: user3.id, book_id: book193.id })
Review.create({ title: "Quick and Sexy read!!", rating: 4, body: "&#34;He's looking at me the way I'd always wished he would when I was younger.&#34;Nothing like a life-long crush becoming a whirlwind romance!!Remy had been pining over Deacon for years, and now that he's back in town, and she's finally old enough for him, she wants the chance. But will he even notice the woman she has become?Deacon just got out of an awful marriage and is now a single father. Needing a babysitter, he calls on the one girl he knows and trusts. But she's not that little girl anymore. She's grown, hot as sin, and he can't get her off his mind.&#34;I want her. I want her more than I've ever wanted anyone before. I need to claim her. She has to be mine.&#34;This was a quick and sexy read full of passion and love. It teaches us that no matter the time, or age, love happens when it's right.For Remy and Deacon, life had to teach them a few lessons first;)Great read!!!&#34;I...I think I've fallen for you.&#34;&#34;You finally caught up. I fell for you long ago.&#34;", user_id: user4.id, book_id: book193.id })
Review.create({ title: "People actually liked this?", rating: 2, body: "This was a short read of less than 100 pages with the word &#34;babysitter&#34; in the title.  So, no, I wasn't expecting Shakespeare.  But OMG this was bad!  Like, I can't make eye contact with myself in the mirror bad.  Like, I wish this were Audible so I could get my listener credit back bad.  Did I mention it was bad?  I was hopeful at first because, grammatically, the writing was pretty good -- better than I expected.  But after the cute opening scene, everything went to creepy next-door neighbor hell.  The &#34;romance&#34; between Remy and Deacon was rushed and inauthentic, without even the pretense of an emotional connection.  It just felt dirty and wrong.  Her eagerness to get pregnant and be an 18 year-old mother and wife, and his willingness to do it, made my skin crawl.  And, while the author uses Deacon's backstory with his ex-wife to paint him as a victim, it actually has the opposite effect.  So we see the current situation as just another link in Deacon's poor judgment chain.  As for Remy's mother, I don't know a parent alive who would push her beloved daughter into the arms of the recently divorced skeevy 30 year-old neighbor.  This whole book just felt sad.", user_id: user5.id, book_id: book193.id })
Review.create({ title: "Sweet and saucy", rating: 5, body: "I  loved this story! Of course I love a happy ending, and this story delivered, but I also loved the twists along the way to get there. Remy is sweet, and mature for her age, and despite being sexy isn't skanky (a nice change of pace for once). Deacon is panty melting hot, not just with looks but his devotion to his daughter, and his desire to provide a stable and loving home for his daughter (I could feel my hormones sighing), and Remy.A great, light, quick read! Grab yourself a copy!", user_id: user6.id, book_id: book193.id })
