Review.create({ title: "quick hot read", rating: 4, body: "I love reading about single sexy dads. Deacon is sexy, sweet and a single dad. Remy has always had a crush on Deacon since she was a teenager. Now that she's grown up those feelings have gotten deeper, especially since she became his babysitter. Pretty soon the lines blur and they both stop fighting it.Get ready ladies this book heats up quickly and will scorch you in the best way.", user_id: user8.id, book_id: book193.id })
book194 = Book.create({ title: "Hard Road (Jon Reznick Thriller Series Book 1)", author: "J. B. Turner", image_url: "https://res.cloudinary.com/dt72mzjpx/image/upload/book_194.jpg", publisher: "Thomas & Mercer ", date: "August 16, 2016", description: " Jon Reznick is a &#x201c;ghost&#x201d;: a black-ops specialist who takes his orders from shadowy handlers, and his salary from the US government. Still mourning the loss of his beloved wife on 9/11, he&#x2019;s dispatched to carry out a high-level hit. Reznick knows only that it must look like suicide. It&#x2019;s textbook.But the target is not the man Reznick expected. The whole setup is wrong. In an instant the operation is compromised, and Reznick is on the run with the man he was sent to kill. A man wanted by the FBI, and by a mysterious terrorist organization hell-bent on bringing the United States to its knees. FBI Assistant Director Martha Meyerstein is determined to track him down, and to intercept whatever it is Reznick was sent to do.When Reznick&#x2019;s young daughter becomes a pawn in the game, he has to use more than his military training to stay one step ahead of those responsible. Meanwhile, he is the only person who knows the true extent of the threat to national security&#x2014;and has the stealth and determination to stop it.Revised edition: This edition of Hard Road includes editorial revisions.", amazon_link: "https://www.amazon.com/Hard-Road-Reznick-Thriller-Book-ebook/dp/B01DYC10NG", kobo_link: "https://www.kobo.com/us/en/search?query=Hard%20Road%20(Jon%20Reznick%20Thriller%20Series%20Book%201)%20J.%20B.%20Turner", play_link: "https://play.google.com/store/search?c=books&hl=en&q=Hard%20Road%20(Jon%20Reznick%20Thriller%20Series%20Book%201)%20J.%20B.%20Turner" })
Review.create({ title: "Pretty good entry in the lone hero thriller genre, except...", rating: 3, body: "I have mixed feelings about this book.  The story is chocked full of action, intrigue, high-tech gadgets, shadowy government types who may or may not have America's best interests at heart, and straight-shooting good guys (and women) who have to figure out ways to work together.  Hero Jon Reznick is cut from the same cloth as Mitch Rapp, Court Gentry, or Will Robie, a seasoned professional operating in the high-stakes world of espionage, black sites, and assassinations, complete with a tragic back story and a young daughter he tries to shield from his grim work.  So, no complaints here.The biggest problem I had with the book is a technical one; namely, the author repeats many of the same phrases over and over.  And over and over.  I lost count of how many times Reznick &#34;felt a surge of anger&#34; or a &#34;rising tide of anger,&#34; how often his &#34;mind flashed back&#34; to something, only for him to be &#34;snapped out of his reverie&#34; by a sudden sound, how the characters continually started their sentences with the word &#34;look,&#34; as in &#34;Look, I'm telling you&#34; or &#34;Look, here's the situation&#34; or &#34;Look, I understand that...&#34; and so on.  And I have never read a story where the characters sigh so much.  The last third of the book was filled to the brim with &#34;He sighed,&#34; &#34;A long drawn out sigh,&#34; &#34;She sighed loudly.&#34;  I'm amazed they didn't all pass out, they were expelling so much carbon dioxide.  The repetition of the same phrases became such a distraction that I couldn't enjoy the book as much as I would have liked.  A good editor should be able to give things that final polish.All in all, a solid thriller that will keep you occupied as you lie on the beach or wait for your flight in an airport lounge.  I just hope you're able to shut off that part of your brain that notices patterns or you might have a &#34;hard road&#34; ahead of you.  Cautiously recommended.", user_id: user1.id, book_id: book194.id })
Review.create({ title: "Hurricane Reznick is Coming Thru.", rating: 5, body: "Hurricane Reznick Smashes Through Former Special Ops agent Jon Reznick has retired and found the only freelance job he's really fitted for is as an assassin. (it's sort of like being unemployed and becoming a writer but less complicated, I suppose) In the final moments of a job, he talks to the victim (never a good idea) and begins to have doubts.In order to ensure that his doubts don't spoil his otherwise perfect record, someone kidnaps his daughter.&#34;Someone&#34; made a very bad mistake.Reznick, who really sort of reminds me of the Juggernaut from the old Spiderman comics, tucks the intended victim under his arm, and goes hunting. OK, he mostly tucks the guy in the trunk but the imagery was better the other way. Like the Incredible Hulk (I'm going with the Marvel Comics analogies and you can't stop me) he pummels people, cars, and small buildings all the way down the East coast on a steady diet of Dexadrine and coffee.I do have to remark that this is an error on J.B.Turner's part. I know from personal experience that when you work past 72 hours straight, regardless of the amount of various chemicals you may use, you end up in the hospital. Yes, that ward where they lock the elevator.But that's a minor quibble. Turner flips constantly between Reznick and the FBI team trying to bring him down. It's like the way The Wire portrayed both dealers and cops as tough people--just in different lines of work. The dialog is excellent and Turner describes Washington DC so accurately that I was thinking of having a cup of coffee with him until I learned he lives in England. (My novel, &#34;Courier,&#34; and &#34;Hard Road&#34; are both published by Exhibit A)It's a cliche to say &#34;the action never stops&#34; but in Hard Road, it really NEVER stops and the number of destroyed vehicles gets close to &#34;Fast and Furious&#34; levels. But it's all completely believable and totally engrossing. I read it straight through and enjoyed every page.", user_id: user2.id, book_id: book194.id })
Review.create({ title: "One awesome read.", rating: 5, body: "A great read. Spoiler alert for those who don't want to know what the books about.This one starts with Jon Reznick at his home in Rockland, Maine.Reznick is ex Delta Force and was involved in black ops all over the world working for the CIA.Reznick still works in black ops and his handler is a man named Maddox. A Maddox he's never met and who's only a voice for missions and instructions.Reznick is an assassin who takes out sh**bag terrorists who masquerade as businessmen and world leaders. Its a lucrative business and is something Reznick is very, very good at. Killing and surviving.Reznick lost his wife when the Twin Towers collapsed on 9-11. She was an attorney who worked in the South tower. Reznick has an eleven year old daughter named Lauren and the with help of his Mother-in-law, Beth, he managed to survive the death of his wife.  Jon needed loads of help because the death of his wife almost tore him apart. Beth is a great lady and her help was immeasurable.Right now Maddox, Jon's handler, has called. There is a package that needs taking out and Reznick agrees to the mission.Once inside the mans hotel room, Jon is getting ready to kill him when he spots tags around his neck. Military?? On reading them he finds the name Benjamin Luntz, IDF. Isreali Defense Force. Reznick decides he needs to speak with this man.It takes eight minutes for the man to wake up after Jon had sedated him. The man says his name is Frank Luntz. Benjamin was his son. A son who killed when and IED exploded in Isreal. Lunts says he's a Govt. Scientist and he has a Federal minder in the bedroom adjoining his. The minder is there because Frank has info he desperately needs to give to the FBI and that he had a meeting in the morning to give that info.Jon checks the other bedroom and finds the Federal Agent dead. Who killed him and why? Jon has no idea but decides he and Luntz need to get out of the hotel and Jon needs to figure out just what the hell he's gotten himself involved in.So begins one damned fine read.This one has Jon, Luntz, Martha Meyerstein an Assistan FBI Director who's leading the hunt for Reznick and Luntz, a plan involving a Lt. Col. Caan that will leave thousands dead, Thomas Wesley a former member of the NSA who discovered something he tried to tell his bosses about, bosses who didn't want to listen, information that would have saved the day, a Wesley who was able to pass this info on the Congressman Lance Drake who also did nothing with the info, a Wesley who was ultimately murdered because of that info, the death of Beth, murder, attempted murder, a man named Merceron who hides behind his Diplomatic Immunity, a boat in the Florida keys, Reznicks kidnapped daughter, Reznicks good friend and ex-Delta operator Ligget who's also murdered, a man named MaGruder who also served with Reznick and LIggett, Ligget's son Ron, Tiny another Delta operator who helps Reznick, the FBI, the CIA, Pakistan and Jon Reznick doing his best to find his daughter, avoid the FBI and ultimately save the day.Five Stars and then some.", user_id: user3.id, book_id: book194.id })
book195 = Book.create({ title: "Harry Potter and the Half-Blood Prince", author: "J.K. Rowling", image_url: "https://res.cloudinary.com/dt72mzjpx/image/upload/book_195.jpg", publisher: "Pottermore from J.K. Rowling; Reprint edition ", date: "December 8, 2015", description: " &#x22;There it was, hanging in the sky above the school: the blazing green skull with a serpent tongue, the mark Death Eaters left behind whenever they had entered a building &#x2026; wherever they had murdered &#x2026;&#x22;When Dumbledore arrives at Privet Drive one summer night to collect Harry Potter, his wand hand is blackened and shrivelled, but he does not reveal why. Secrets and suspicion are spreading through the wizarding world, and Hogwarts itself is not safe. Harry is convinced that Malfoy bears the Dark Mark: there is a Death Eater amongst them. Harry will need powerful magic and true friends as he explores Voldemort's darkest secrets, and Dumbledore prepares him to face his destiny ...", amazon_link: "https://www.amazon.com/Harry-Potter-Half-Blood-Prince-Rowling-ebook/dp/B0192CTMWI", kobo_link: "https://www.kobo.com/us/en/ebook/harry-potter-and-the-prisoner-of-azkaban-6", play_link: "https://play.google.com/store/books/details/Patrizia_Hannemann_The_Greek_Mythology_in_Harry_Po?id=KjdTCAAAQBAJ" })
